\taxon{Definition}

\p{Consider the [oppositization 2-functor] (?) #{(-)^\mathsf{op} :\Cat^{\mathsf{op}}\to \mathsf{Cat}}. Given a [double category](math-000D) #{D}, sending it via this [2-functor](math-001Q) we get another double category. It is called the \strong{tightwise opposite} of #{D} and is denoted #{D^{\mathsf{top}}}. }